    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f19c61a5_791508e5",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 53,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T22:38:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I find it strange that Actions set is stored as a list, but roles are stored as a map. I generally believe storing listings as lists are better, since it makes each individual element of the set to be fully described (it has a name and properties). Thus I suggest:\n\n message Role {\n   string role_id \u003d 1;\n   ...\n }\n\n repeated Role roles \u003d 4;\n\nIf you insist on using maps, then make \u0027actions\u0027 a map too... I just don\u0027t understand why actions and roles are stored differently.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 53,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 53,
        "endChar": 16
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
