    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "62515885_c5424087",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T22:38:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMHO, using repeated fields for this is very confusing. It should be \"luci.chromium.try/linux_rel\" instead. Even better, just drop this notion of hierarchies for now, we don\u0027t need it. Let\u0027s keep things simple. A unit of ACLs in Buildbucket is a bucket, not a builder. A unit of ACLs in CIPD is a package (not a package instance), etc.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "368d7cb1_35b6cdc0",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001907
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T22:56:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We went back and forth on this.\n\n  * I claim that we don\u0027t want to do string parsing when we don\u0027t need to, and I don\u0027t like the idea of having all services needing to implement some weird parser for the resource rules. Don\u0027t do string formatting and parsing when you don\u0027t need to.\n  * Unfortunately, `single -\u003e repeated` is only a backwards compatible change in the binary proto, not in JSON, and not in any of the generated code (especially in python where str and list are both iterable).\n\nSo the conclusion was what\u0027s here; We have a single kind (static string), which names the resource type, and then the arguments are individual strings. This way neither the caller nor the service need to do any formatting/parsing operations, and it gets us out of dumb stuff where some resources have slashes in their names.",
      "parentUuid": "62515885_c5424087",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2b8b3468_31555420",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T23:00:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I believe some string manipulation in cases we don\u0027t have as of now is a better evil than this confusion. I agree to make the batching version of this API by accepting names of distinct resources in this field.",
      "parentUuid": "368d7cb1_35b6cdc0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2599cc89_5e4a94aa",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T23:01:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Then we can probably rename \u0027resource_name\u0027 to \u0027resource_path\u0027 and say that \"it is always of length 1 currently\". AFAIK, we have no hierarchical resources currently.\n\nEven so, we won\u0027t be able to get away from string parsing. Most of our APIs are REST APIs. If we have a resource with name [\u0027A\u0027, \u0027B\u0027, \u0027C\u0027] we will need a way to target it in REST call. So we\u0027ll HAVE to use string parsing...",
      "parentUuid": "368d7cb1_35b6cdc0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5c9146a9_05ada3fe",
        "filename": "common/proto/access/access.proto",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-08-31T23:08:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if it is a path, then kind should be a part of that path, and then we are going back to the original single string field \"resource\".\n\nI am OK with any of\n1) one repeated \"resource\" field, has some string math, e.g. [\"bucket/luci.chromium.try\"]. Repeated b/c batching\n2) one repeated message field with fields (kind, id), e.g. [{kind: \"bucket\", id: \"luci.chromium.try\"}]\n3) one optional field \"kind\" and repeated \"resource_args\", repeated b/c batching, not hierarchy.",
      "parentUuid": "2599cc89_5e4a94aa",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "0d2eb969effc180f3629bc4788816677c771999e",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
